It is the first time since the outbreak of the COVID-19 pandemic more than two years ago, that the event is taking place in person. About 4 000 delegates are expected to attend. The indaba is expected to generate around R 72.5 million ($4.49 billion) income for the city’s economy. This year’s indaba will focus among other things, on recovery from the pandemic, opportunities to combine business and leisure tourism, and enhancing intra-African travel and tourism. --SABC--